---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
const title = "Vision-Based Control";
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout
  title={`${title} | Payload Yaw Control`}
  lang="en"
  prevHref={`${base}/en/yaw_estimation/`}
  prevLabel="Yaw Estimation"
  nextHref={`${base}/en/summary`}
  nextLabel="Summary"
>
  <article class="detail-page">
    <h1>{title}</h1>
    <p>
      The Yaw estimation model and the payload Yaw control model were integrated
      to demonstrate a vision-based payload Yaw control system on a Raspberry Pi.
      Its control performance was then compared with that of the development
      environment.
    </p>    
    <nav class="page-nav" aria-label="Page navigation">
      <div class="page-nav-row">
        <span>Environment:</span>
        <a href="#environment">Raspberry Pi Environment</a>
        <a href="#system">System Configuration</a>
      </div>
      <div class="page-nav-row">
        <span>Results:</span>
        <a href="#result-overview">Evaluation Method</a>
        <a href="#hsteel">HSteel</a>
        <a href="#plate">Plate</a>
        <a href="#truss">Truss</a>
      </div>
    </nav>

    <section id="environment" class="content-section">
      <h2>Raspberry Pi Environment</h2>
      <p>
        A Raspberry Pi was used as the controller.
        The camera images used as control inputs were generated by a 3D simulator
        running on a Linux workstation.
        The simulator updates each rendered frame based on the simulation state received from the Raspberry Pi.
      </p>
      <div class="environment-grid">
        <figure>
          <img
            src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/raspberry_pi/raspberry_pi.jpg`}
            alt="Raspberry Pi used as the controller"
          />
          <figcaption>
            <span class="figure-title">Raspberry Pi</span>
            Runs the Yaw estimation model and the payload Yaw control model.            
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure>
          <img
            src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/raspberry_pi/environment.jpg`}
            alt="Experimental setup connecting the Raspberry Pi and the 3D simulator"
          />
          <figcaption>
            <span class="figure-title">Experimental Setup</span>
            The Raspberry Pi communicates with the 3D simulator via Wi-Fi.
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="system" class="content-section">
      <h2>System Configuration</h2>
      <p>
        All estimation and control processes, except for 3D rendering,
        were executed on the Raspberry Pi.
      </p>
      <figure class="system-figure">
        <img
          src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/raspberry_pi/system_flow_en.png`}
          alt="System architecture of the vision-based payload Yaw control system"
        />
        <figcaption>
          Communication and processing flow between the 3D simulator and the Raspberry Pi.
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
      <div class="system-description">
        <div>
          <h3>3D Simulator</h3>
          <p>
            Generates the payload images used for Yaw estimation and sends them
            to the Raspberry Pi.
            The control model outputs commands for the four thrusters.
            The resulting simulation state is then sent to the 3D simulator
            for rendering.            
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>Raspberry Pi</h3>
          <p>
            Estimates the payload Yaw angle from the input image and feeds the
            estimated value into the payload Yaw control model.
            The control model outputs the commands for the four thrusters,
            which are then sent to the 3D simulator.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="result-overview" class="content-section">
      <h2>Evaluation Method</h2>
      <p>
        Control experiments were conducted for HSteel, Plate, and Truss under the
        X1Y1 condition, which represents the strongest disturbance condition.
        The payload Yaw response and thruster output patterns were compared between
        the development environment and the Raspberry Pi environment.      
      </p>
      <div class="chart-guide">
        <div>
          <span class="chart-guide-title">Baseline</span>
          <p>Payload Yaw angle without control.</p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <span class="chart-guide-title">Control</span>
          <p>Payload Yaw angle during control and the 90° target angle.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <span class="chart-guide-title">Thruster Force Heatmap</span>
          <p>Outputs of the four thrusters. Brighter colors indicate higher thrust.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <span class="chart-guide-title">Animation</span>
          <p>Visual confirmation of the payload motion during control.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="hsteel" class="content-section result-section">
      <h2>HSteel</h2>
      <p>
        Payload Yaw control was evaluated using the HSteel payload.
        In the Raspberry Pi environment, the payload reached the target angle
        approximately 10 seconds after control started and then remained close to 90°.
      </p>
      <div class="result-grid">
        <figure>
          <img
            src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/raspberry_pi/HSteel_X1Y1.png`}
            alt="HSteel control results in the development environment"
          />
          <figcaption>
            <span class="figure-title">Development Environment</span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure class="raspberry-result">
          <img
            src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/raspberry_pi/HSteel_Pi.png`}
            alt="HSteel control results on the Raspberry Pi"
          />
          <figcaption>
            <span class="figure-title">Raspberry Pi</span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
      <div class="result-summary">
        Control performance on the Raspberry Pi was comparable to that of the
        development environment.
      </div>      
      <div class="hero-video">
        <video controls muted playsinline preload="metadata">
          <source
            src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/videos/runtime_HSteel_0001-1800.mp4`}
            type="video/mp4"
          />
          Your browser does not support HTML5 video.
        </video>
      </div>	        
    </section>

    <section id="plate" class="content-section result-section">
      <h2>Plate</h2>
      <p>
        Payload Yaw control was evaluated using the Plate payload.
        In the Raspberry Pi environment, the payload reached the target angle
        in approximately 13 seconds and then remained close to 90°.      
      </p>
      <div class="result-grid">
        <figure>
          <img
            src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/raspberry_pi/Plate_X1Y1.png`}
            alt="Plate control results in the development environment"
          />
          <figcaption>
            <span class="figure-title">Development Environment</span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure class="raspberry-result">
          <img
            src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/raspberry_pi/Plate_Pi.png`}
            alt="Plate control results on the Raspberry Pi"
          />
          <figcaption>
            <span class="figure-title">Raspberry Pi</span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
      <div class="result-summary">
        Control performance on the Raspberry Pi was comparable to that of the
        development environment.
      </div>
      <div class="hero-video">
        <video controls muted playsinline preload="metadata">
          <source
            src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/videos/runtime_Plate_0001-1800.mp4`}
            type="video/mp4"
          />
          Your browser does not support HTML5 video.
        </video>
      </div>	        
    </section>

    <section id="truss" class="content-section result-section">
      <h2>Truss</h2>
      <p>
        Payload Yaw control was evaluated using the Truss payload.
        In the Raspberry Pi environment, the payload took longer to reach the target
        than in the development environment, reaching the target Yaw angle at around
        60 seconds.
        Nevertheless, the payload ultimately reached the target angle and maintained
        its orientation.
      </p>      
      <div class="result-grid">
        <figure>
          <img
            src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/raspberry_pi/Truss_X1Y1.png`}
            alt="Truss control results in the development environment"
          />
          <figcaption>
            <span class="figure-title">Development Environment</span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure class="raspberry-result">
          <img
            src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/images/raspberry_pi/Truss_Pi.png`}
            alt="Truss control results on the Raspberry Pi"
          />
          <figcaption>
            <span class="figure-title">Raspberry Pi</span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
      <div class="truss-notes">
        <p>
          Although the thruster output pattern was similar to that of the
          development environment, the payload required more time to reach the
          target Yaw angle.
        </p>
        <p>
          This difference is considered to be caused by errors in payload Yaw
          estimation. <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/en/yaw_estimation/#max-error`}>
            Truss / X1Y1 produced the largest Yaw estimation error
          </a>,
          and even small estimation errors affected the output of the control model.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="result-summary">
        Although the Truss payload required more time to reach the target,
        the system running on the Raspberry Pi ultimately reached and maintained
        the target payload Yaw angle.
      </div>      
      <div class="hero-video">
        <video controls muted playsinline preload="metadata">
          <source
            src={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/videos/runtime_Truss_0001-1800.mp4`}
            type="video/mp4"
          />
          Your browser does not support HTML5 video.
        </video>
      </div>	        
    </section>

    <section class="content-section conclusion-section">
      <h2>Evaluation Results</h2>
      <div class="summary-box">
        The integrated Yaw estimation and payload Yaw control system was successfully
        executed on the Raspberry Pi.
        Target Yaw control was achieved for all three payloads: HSteel, Plate,
        and Truss.
        HSteel and Plate showed performance comparable to that of the development
        environment, while the Truss payload required more time to reach the target
        Yaw angle but ultimately achieved stable control.
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .detail-page {
    padding: 32px 0 64px;
  }

  .detail-page > h1 {
    margin: 0 0 20px;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .detail-page > p {
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.9;
  }

  .page-nav {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 12px;
    margin: 32px 0 56px;
    padding: 16px 0;
    border-top: 1px solid #ddd;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;
  }

  .page-nav-row {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 6px 18px;
  }

  .page-nav-row span {
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .content-section {
    scroll-margin-top: 32px;
    margin-bottom: 62px;
  }

  .content-section h2 {
    margin: 0 0 20px;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .content-section h3 {
    margin: 0 0 10px;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .content-section > p {
    margin: 0 0 28px;
    line-height: 1.9;
  }

  figure {
    margin: 0;
  }

  img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
  }

  figcaption {
    margin-top: 12px;
    color: #666;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .figure-title {
    display: block;
    color: #222;
  }

  .environment-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 28px;
    margin-top: 28px;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .environment-grid img {
    aspect-ratio: 16 / 10;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .system-figure {
    max-width: 920px;
    margin: 28px auto 0;
  }

  .system-description {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 32px;
    margin-top: 32px;
  }

  .system-description p {
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.9;
  }

  .chart-guide {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, minmax(0, 1fr));
    border-top: 1px solid #ddd;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;
  }

  .chart-guide > div {
    padding: 16px 20px;
  }

  .chart-guide > div + div {
    border-left: 1px solid #ddd;
  }

  .chart-guide-title {
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .chart-guide p {
    margin: 6px 0 0;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .result-section {
    padding-top: 4px;
  }

  .result-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 32px;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .raspberry-result {
    padding: 10px;
    border: 2px solid #e98524;
  }

  .raspberry-result figcaption {
    margin-bottom: 2px;
  }

  .result-summary {
    margin-top: 28px;
    padding: 12px 14px;
    border-left: 4px solid #e98524;
    background: #fafafa;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .truss-notes {
    margin-top: 28px;
  }

  .truss-notes p {
    margin: 0 0 14px;
    line-height: 1.9;
  }

  .summary-box {
    padding: 14px 16px;
    border: 2px solid #999;
    background: #fafafa;
    line-height: 1.9;
  }

  .detail-navigation {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 24px;
    padding-top: 24px;
    border-top: 1px solid #ddd;
  }

  .detail-navigation a {
    color: inherit;
  }

  .hero-video {
    width: 90%;
    max-width: 1100px;
    margin: 20px auto;
    border: none;
    outline: none;
    box-shadow: none;
  }

  .hero-video video {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
  }


  @media (max-width: 700px) {
    .detail-page {
      padding-top: 24px;
    }

    .page-nav {
      margin-bottom: 44px;
    }

    .content-section {
      margin-bottom: 56px;
    }

    .environment-grid,
    .system-description,
    .result-grid,
    .chart-guide {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .environment-grid {
      gap: 36px;
    }

    .environment-grid img {
      aspect-ratio: auto;
      object-fit: contain;
    }

    .chart-guide > div + div {
      border-left: 0;
      border-top: 1px solid #ddd;
    }

    .result-grid {
      gap: 28px;
    }

    .detail-navigation {
      flex-direction: column;
    }

    .hero-video {
      width: 100%;
      margin-top: 28px;
    }    
  }
</style>